    <titleInfo lang="en" type="translated">
        <title>The Letters in the Dreams</title>
    </titleInfo>
    <titleInfo type="reference">
        <title>Ishimure 1986a</title>
    </titleInfo>
    <abstract>[Taishan][JSY]:
        Ishimure saw a dream from time to time, where she stands at a river. Random paperclips with unrecognizable letters are floating away. She identified one of those letters she saw as the character jing/jō 浄 from JSY, once she read an article called “Kodai Chūgoku no magaihi 古代中国の摩崖碑 []” from SAITŌ Yoshishige 斎藤義重 and HIDAI Nankoku 比田井南谷. A link to the article in the NDL Digital Collection: 
        (芸術新潮. 28巻5号　通巻329号　1977年5月):
        https://dl.ndl.go.jp/info:ndljp/pid/6048580?tocOpened=1</abstract>
